{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}

{% block title %}{{ 'privacy_policy'|trans }}{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
    <div class="col-lg-12">
        <div class="d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center mx-3">
            <h1 class="display-6">
                <span class="d-lg-inline">{{ 'privacy_policy'|trans }}</span>
            </h1>
            <img src="{{ asset('images/logo.png') }}" alt="logo" class="img-fluid logo-s">
        </div>

        <hr>

        <div class="main container mt-4 small">
            <div class="card shadow-sm">
                <div class="card-body p-4 p-md-5">
                    <h2 class="text-center mb-4">Privacy Policy – SF Project Starter</h2>
                    <p class="text-muted text-center">Effective date: #</p>

                    <p class="mb-4">SF Project Starter ("we", "our", or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your personal information when you use our Website.</p>

                    <h5 class="mb-2">1. Information We Collect</h5>
                    <ul class="list-unstyled ps-3">
                        <li class="mb-2"><i class="bi bi-dot"></i> Personal information (name, email address)</li>
                        <li class="mb-2"><i class="bi bi-dot"></i> Account information (login credentials)</li>
                        <li class="mb-2"><i class="bi bi-dot"></i> Usage data (pages visited, features used)</li>
                        <li class="mb-2"><i class="bi bi-dot"></i>  Text data and images you input for translation, transcription, and analysis – these are processed automatically using AI systems and are not stored permanently unless you explicitly choose to save the result.</li>
                        <li class="mb-2"><i class="bi bi-dot"></i> IP address and device information</li>
                        <li class="mb-2"><i class="bi bi-dot"></i> Cookies and similar tracking technologies</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h5 class="mb-2 mt-4">2. Legal Basis for Processing (GDPR)</h5>
                    <p>We process your personal data on the following legal grounds:</p>
                    <ul class="list-unstyled ps-3">
                        <li class="mb-2"><i class="bi bi-dot"></i> Your consent (which you can withdraw at any time)</li>
                        <li class="mb-2"><i class="bi bi-dot"></i> Performance of our contract with you</li>
                        <li class="mb-2"><i class="bi bi-dot"></i> Our legitimate business interests that include improving our services, ensuring security and preventing fraud</li>
                        <li class="mb-2"><i class="bi bi-dot"></i> Compliance with legal obligations such as accounting or regulatory requirements</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h5 class="mb-2 mt-4">3. How We Use Your Information</h5>
                    <ul class="list-unstyled ps-3">
                        <li class="mb-2"><i class="bi bi-dot"></i> To provide and improve our services</li>
                        <li class="mb-2"><i class="bi bi-dot"></i> To communicate with you about your account or our services</li>
                        <li class="mb-2"><i class="bi bi-dot"></i> To process translations, transcriptions, and analyses using our systems and third-party APIs</li>
                        <li class="mb-2"><i class="bi bi-dot"></i> To save your history and preferences</li>
                        <li class="mb-2"><i class="bi bi-dot"></i> For security and fraud prevention</li>
                        <li class="mb-2"><i class="bi bi-dot"></i> For legal compliance</li>
                        <li class="mb-2"><i class="bi bi-dot"></i> For analytics and service improvement</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h5 class="mb-2 mt-4">4. Data Sharing and Third-Party Services</h5>
                    <p>We do not sell your data. We may share data with:</p>
                    <ul class="list-unstyled ps-3">
                        <li class="mb-2"><i class="bi bi-dot"></i> OpenAI (for processing transcriptions, translations and text analysis)</li>
                        <li class="mb-2"><i class="bi bi-dot"></i> Hostinger (our hosting provider)</li>
                        <li class="mb-2"><i class="bi bi-dot"></i> Other service providers essential to delivering our services</li>
                        <li class="mb-2"><i class="bi bi-dot"></i> Authorities if legally required</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h5 class="mb-2 mt-4">5. International Data Transfers</h5>
                    <p>Your data may be processed in countries outside your country of residence, including countries outside the European Economic Area (EEA). These transfers are subject to appropriate safeguards such as Standard Contractual Clauses or adequacy decisions by the European Commission.</p>

                    <h5 class="mb-2 mt-4">6. Data Retention</h5>
                    <p>We retain your personal data for as long as necessary to provide our services and fulfill the purposes described in this policy, unless a longer retention period is required by law. Account data is retained while your account remains active. You can request deletion of your data at any time.</p>

                    <h5 class="mb-2 mt-4">7. Cookies and Analytics</h5>
                    <p>We use cookies and similar technologies to understand usage patterns and improve our service. You can manage cookie preferences through your browser settings. We may use analytics services such as Google Analytics to help us understand how users interact with our application.</p>

                    <h5 class="mb-2 mt-4">8. Your Privacy Rights</h5>
                    <ul class="list-unstyled ps-3">
                        <li class="mb-2"><i class="bi bi-dot"></i> Right to access your personal data</li>
                        <li class="mb-2"><i class="bi bi-dot"></i> Right to rectification (correction) of your data</li>
                        <li class="mb-2"><i class="bi bi-dot"></i> Right to erasure ("right to be forgotten")</li>
                        <li class="mb-2"><i class="bi bi-dot"></i> Right to restrict processing</li>
                        <li class="mb-2"><i class="bi bi-dot"></i> Right to data portability</li>
                        <li class="mb-2"><i class="bi bi-dot"></i> Right to object to processing</li>
                        <li class="mb-2"><i class="bi bi-dot"></i> Right to withdraw consent</li>
                        <li class="mb-2"><i class="bi bi-dot"></i> Right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority</li>
                        <li class="mb-2"><i class="bi bi-dot"></i> These rights apply to users located in the EEA. Users in other regions may have similar rights under their local privacy laws.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>To exercise your rights, please contact us at <a href="#">info@sf-project-starter.com</a>. We will respond to requests within 30 days.</p>

                    <h5 class="mb-2 mt-4">9. Data Security</h5>
                    <p>We implement appropriate technical and organizational security measures to protect your data from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, and destruction. However, no internet transmission is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>

                    <h5 class="mb-2 mt-4">10. Your Responsibilities</h5>
                    <p>If you submit content that includes personal data of third parties, you are responsible for ensuring that you have the necessary rights or consent to process such data through our services.</p>

                    <h5 class="mb-2 mt-4">11. Children's Privacy</h5>
                    <p>Our services are not intended for individuals under the age of 16. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children. If we become aware that we have collected personal data from a child without parental consent, we will take steps to delete that information.</p>

                    <h5 class="mb-2 mt-4">12. Data Breach Notification</h5>
                    <p>In the event of a personal data breach that is likely to result in a risk to your rights and freedoms, we will notify you and relevant supervisory authorities in accordance with applicable law.</p>

                    <h5 class="mb-2 mt-4">13. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h5>
                    <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The updated version will be indicated by an updated "Last updated" date and will be effective immediately upon posting. We will notify you of material changes via email or through a notification within our application.</p>

                    <h5 class="mb-2 mt-4">14. Contact Us</h5>
                    <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us at:</p>
                    <address class="mb-3">
                        <strong>SF Project Starter</strong><br>
                        Email: <a href="#">info@sf-project-starter.com</a>
                    </address>

                    <div class="text-muted text-center pt-3 border-top">
                        <small>Last updated: #</small>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
{% endblock %}
